MotorcycleLib.description: Free Modelica library for the purpose of simulation, analysis and control of bicycles and motorcycles (single-track vehicles, uses BondLib)

NCLib.description: Free library for combined simulation of networks and controllers in the domain of automation systems.

ModelicaDEVS.description: A free library for discrete-event modeling using the DEVS formalism. (unlicensed)

SPICELib.description: Free library with some of the modeling and analysis capabilities of the electric circuit simulator PSPICE.

BondGraph.description: Free library for graphical Bond Graph modelling that contains common standard linear elements, sensors, and specific non-linear elements, especially for hydraulic networks.

ComplexLib.description: Free library for steady-state analysis of AC circuits within phasor domain.

Modelica_EnergyStorages.description: Free library that contains models with different complexity for simulating of electric energy storages like batteries (single cells as well as stacks) interacting with loads, battery management systems, loads and charging devices.

FuelCellLib.description: Free library to model fuel cells (unlicensed)

DESLib.description: Free library for Parallel DEVS and Process-Oriented Modeling in Modelica

BondLib.description: Free library to model physical systems with bond graphs.

Modelica_DeviceDrivers.description: Free (standard conform) library for interfacing hardware drivers to Modelica models. There is support for joysticks, keyboards, UDP, shared memory, AD/DA converters and other devices.

HelmholtzMedia.description: Fluid properties for Modelica, for pure fluids that can be described by a Helmholtz energy equation of state

IndustrialControlSystems.description: Modelica Industrial Control Systems Library by Politecnico di Milano

BioChem.description: Free library for biochemical modeling and simulation with Modelica.

Modelica_LinearSystems2.description: Free library providing different representations of linear, time invariant differential and difference equation systems, as well as typical operations on these system descriptions.

ExtendedPetriNets.description: Free library to model Petri nets and state transition diagrams (extended version).

WasteWater.description: Free library for modelling and simulation of waste water treatment plants.

LinearMPC.description: Library for model-based predictive controllers with linear process models.

MultiBondLib.description: Free library to model physical systems with multi-bond graphs.

MotorcycleDynamics.description: Free library for the dynamic simulation of a motorcycle, and tailored to test and validation of active control systems for motorcycle dynamics.

Modelica_StateGraph2.description: Free library providing components to model discrete event, reactive and hybrid systems in a convenient way with deterministic hierarchical state diagrams. Modelica_StateGraph2 is not fully Modelica compliant and will never be, since a better solution is now available with Modelica 3.3

PowerSystems.description: The library is intended to model electrical power systems at different levels of detail both in transient and steady-state mode.

SPOT.description: Free library providing components to model power systems both in transient and steady-state mode.

WheelsAndTires.description: Free Modelica package providing the easily modifiable tire models. (uses BondLib and MultiBondLib)

PDELib.description: A free library for modeling systems described by 1D partial differential equations. (unlicensed)

ThermoPower.description: Free library to model thermal power plants (based on Modelica.Media)

Modelica.description: Free (standard conform) library from the Modelica Association to model mechanical (1D/3D), electrical (analog, digital, machines), thermal, fluid, control systems and hierarchical state machines. Also numerical functions and functions for strings, files and streams are included.

Verif.description: A free library for verifying the ModelicaSpice library (part of BondLib).

ADGenKinetics.description: Modeling biochemical reaction networks with generalized kinetic formats with capabilities for computing parameter sensitivities using algorithmic differentiation techniques.

RealTimeCoordinationLibrary.description: Enables modeling asynchronous and synchronous communication and rich real-time constraints for complex coordination protocols.

ExternalMedia.description: The ExternalMedia library provides a framework for interfacing external codes computing fluid properties to Modelica.Media-compatible component models.

Modelica_Synchronous.description: Free (standard conform) library to precisely define and synchronize sampled data systems with different sampling rates. It provides convenient to use blocks to utilize the new synchronous language elements introduced in Modelica 3.3.

NeuralNetwork.description: Free library that provides a neural network mathematical model. (unlicensed)

ThermoBondLib.description: Free library library that is designed as a graphical library for modeling convective flows using the thermo-bond graph metaphor (uses BondLib)

OpenHydraulics.description: A free Modelica package providing components describing 1-dimensional fluid flow in hydraulic circuits.

ATplus.description: Free library for Building Simulation and Building Control, fuzzy control library included. (unlicensed)

QSSFluidFlow.description: Free library for quasi steady-state fluid pipe flow.

SystemDynamics.description: Free library for modeling according to the principles of system dynamics of J. Forrester.

FCSys.description: Modelica library of fuel cell models
